title: Static Analysis

android.permission.WAKE_LOCK.description: Allows an application to prevent the phone from going to sleep.

android.permission.ACCESS_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the status of all networks.

android.permission.ACCESS_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to view the information about the status of Wi-Fi.

android.permission.INTERNET.description: Allows an application to create network sockets.

android.permission.VIBRATE.description: Allows the application to control the vibrator.

android.permission.ACCESS_FINE_LOCATION.description: Access fine location sources, such as the Global Positioning System on the phone, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine where you are and may consume additional battery power.

android.permission.ACCESS_COARSE_LOCATIO.description: Access coarse location sources, such as the mobile network database, to determine an approximate phone location, where available. Malicious applications can use this to determine approximately where you are.

android.permission.RECORD_AUDIO.description: Allows application to access the audio record path.

android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_MULTICAST.description: Allows an application to receive packets not directly addressed to your device. This can be useful when discovering services offered nearby. It uses more power than the non-multicast mode.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH.description: Allows an application to view configuration of the local Bluetooth phone and to make and accept connections with paired devices.

android.permission.BLUETOOTH_ADMIN.description: Allows an application to configure the local Bluetooth phone and to discover and pair with remote devices.

android.permission.GET_ACCOUNTS.description: Allows an application to access the list of accounts known by the phone.

android.permission.USE_CREDENTIALS.info: use the authentication credentials of an account
android.permission.USE_CREDENTIALS.description: Allows an application to request authentication tokens.

android.permission.MANAGE_ACCOUNTS.description: Allows an application to perform operations like adding and removing accounts and deleting their password.

android.permission.AUTHENTICATE_ACCOUNTS.description: Allows an application to use the account authenticator capabilities of the Account Manager, including creating accounts as well as obtaining and setting their passwords.

android.permission.READ_PHONE_STATE.description: Allows the application to access the phone features of the device. An application with this permission can determine the phone number and serial number of this phone, whether a call is active, the number that call is connected to and so on.

android.permission.CHANGE_NETWORK_STATE.description: Allows an application to change the state of network connectivity.

android.permission.WRITE_EXTERNAL_STORAG.description: Allows an application to write to the SD card.

android.permission.READ_EXTERNAL_STORAGE.description: Allows an application to read from SD Card.

android.permission.CHANGE_WIFI_STATE.description: Allows an application to connect to and disconnect from Wi-Fi access points and to make changes to configured Wi-Fi networks.

manifest_analysis.title:
Clear text traffic is Enabled For App
[android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]
manifest_analysis.desc: The app intends to use cleartext network traffic, such as cleartext HTTP, FTP stacks, DownloadManager, and MediaPlayer. The default value for apps that target API level 27 or lower is "true". Apps that target API level 28 or higher default to "false". The key reason for avoiding cleartext traffic is the lack of confidentiality, authenticity, and protections against tampering; a network attacker can eavesdrop on transmitted data and also modify it without being detected.
manifest_analysis.name: Clear text traffic is Enabled For App [android:usesCleartextTraffic=true]

manifest_analysis.title:
App has a Network Security Configuration
[android:networkSecurityConfig]
manifest_analysis.desc: The Network Security Configuration feature lets apps customize their network security settings in a safe, declarative configuration file without modifying app code. These settings can be configured for specific domains and for a specific app.
manifest_analysis.name: App has a Network Security Configuration [android:networkSecurityConfig]

manifest_analysis.title: Launch Mode of Activity (com.amazon.bison.HomeActivity) is not standard.
manifest_analysis.desc: An Activity should not be having the launch mode attribute set to "singleTask/singleInstance" as it becomes root Activity and it is possible for other applications to read the contents of the calling Intent. So it is required to use the "standard" launch mode attribute when sensitive information is included in an Intent.
manifest_analysis.name: Launch Mode of Activity is not standard.

strings: "antenna_connection_body" : "Connect the antenna to Fire TV Recast using the coax cable."
"antenna_direction_body" : "Next you will mount the antenna. We recommend that you mount it facing %1$s to receive the most channels."
"antenna_direction_body_placement_tips" : "We recommend mounting your antenna facing %1$s to receive the most channels."
"antenna_direction_no_location_body_link" : "You can use [[this website]] to help you find the best direction to mount the antenna."
"antenna_tutorial_step_1" : "Now let's find a place to mount your antenna. Here are a few tips."
"antenna_tutorial_step_2" : "Fire TV Recast streams content using Wi-Fi so it does not need to be placed next to your TV. Just make sure there is a strong Wi-Fi signal."
"antenna_tutorial_step_3" : "Higher ground and clear line of sight will help you improve signal quality."
"antenna_tutorial_step_4" : "Indoor antennas work best when mounted on windows."
"antenna_tutorial_step_5" : "Drywall also works, but avoid concrete and metal walls."
"cancel_recording_message" : "Do you want to cancel this recording?"
"channel_report_placement_tips_subheader" : "To improve reception on certain channels try repositioning your antenna."
"channel_scan_cancel_dialog_body" : "You will not see any channels if you cancel now. To restart channel scan later, go to Settings > Fire TV Recast > Channels."
"checklist_title" : "Before you begin, make sure you have everything you need."
"complete_body" : "Check out the video to learn more about your new Fire TV Recast."
"connect_with_ethernet_body" : "Your Fire TV Recast requires an Ethernet cable. Please plug one into the back of your device or make sure that the cable is securely connected."
"connectionFailed" : "Unable to connect to your Amazon Fire TV. Please visit help to troubleshoot your issue."
"delete_recording_consent_dialog_message" : "Are you sure you want to delete this recording?"
"delete_recording_protected_consent_dialog_message" : "This recording is protected from automatic deletion. Are you sure you want to delete this protected recording?"
"device_light_status_blue" : "Please wait another 5 minutes for the LED to pulse white."

"device_light_status_negative_desc" : "The light is another color, or I'm having problems"
"device_light_status_positive_desc" : "The light is pulsing white, or I can't see the light and I've waited %1$d minutes"
"device_list_search_sub_msg" : "This may take up to a minute"
"device_provision_wait_for_ota_desc" : "This may take up to 10 minutes. Please do not unplug your Fire TV Recast. If you exit the app, it will continue to update in the background."
"enable_location_prompt" : "Your location seems to be disabled. We need it to suggest your antenna mounting direction. Do you want to enable it?"

"error_code_channel_receive" : "There was an error while retrieving the channel list. Would you like to try again?"

"error_code_channel_tuner_busy" : "Your chanel scan failed because all resources are in use. Please try again at a later time."

"error_code_connect_to_ap_ethernet_in_use" : "Fire TV Recast is already connect to Ethernet. If you want to use Wi-Fi please unplug the Ethernet cable from Fire TV Recast. Otherwise if you want to use Ethernet please choose ethernet from the list."

"error_code_playback_player_callback_error" : "There was a problem in your playback"

"error_code_playback_player_resource_conflict" : "The was a resource conflict reported on your Fire TV Recast. This generally means your Fire TV Recast is streaming to other devices. If the issue persists reboot your Fire TV Recast in settings."

"error_code_poobe_brand_list_load_failed" : "Unable to load list of product brands"
"error_code_poobe_discovery" : "Make sure your Fire TV Blaster is powered on and within range."

"error_code_ssid_not_found" : "We were unable to find that SSID. Please try another."
"error_code_timeout_waiting_for_ota_complete_text" : "Something is wrong. Please tap to continue and contact Customer Service."
"error_code_uncategorized_wifi_error" : "Something has gone wrong. Check your WiFi network and try again."
"error_code_unknown" : "An unknown error has occurred. Please try again."
"error_code_unsupported_android_version" : "Your device's Android version is not supported. Please update your operating system to Lollipop (5.0) or above, then restart setup."
"error_generic_dvr_command" : "Failed to communicate with Fire TV Recast"
"error_schedule_conflict" : "Failed to record program due to a conflict."
"error_search_service" : "There was an error when attempting to search. Please try again."
"error_stb_setup_not_supported_in_country" : "We are sorry, this feature is not available in your country"
"error_unable_to_record_by_invalid_time" : "The program you are trying to record is no longer airing."

"generic_no_network" : "We didn't detect any Wi-Fi networks. Please move your %1$s close to your Wi-Fi router, or enter the network information manually."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

You may be having trouble setting up your Fire TV Blaster. Please try the following;

1. Remove your Fire TV Blaster from it's power adapter for 5 seconds and then make sure is securely plugged to the back.

2. Reboot your phone and try the setup again.

If the problem still persists please contact Amazon Technical Support."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "To factory reset your Fire TV Blaster, follow these steps. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. When the LED is flashing blue and cyan, you will be able to set up your Fire TV Blaster again."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset."

"poobe_ir_command_power_on_main" : "Tap the button above to turn your %1$s back on. This could take a few seconds."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_down_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn down."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn up."
"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Make sure Fire TV Blaster is plugged into an outlet. Wait for the light on the front of Fire TV Blaster to flash blue and cyan. This may take up to two minutes."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

If you don't see a light in front of Fire TV Blaster, it could be either powered off or already connected to the internet. Quickly press and release the button at the bottom of Fire TV Blaster. If the light does not react, it means Fire TV Blaster is powered off.

1. Check that Fire TV Blaster's power adapter is properly connected to a working outlet and the power cable is securely plugged to the back of Fire TV Blaster.

2. If it was powered off, it will turn on and the light will quickly blink blue three times to indicate it has successfully booted up.

3. When you see the light alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

1. Wait for the orange light to stop blinking.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated.

3. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

If you're seeing a blinking purple light, it means Fire TV Blaster has timed out during setup and must be restarted.

1. Unplug the power adapter, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking red, it must be updated.

1. Unplug the power cord, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

4. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will turn off to indicate that your device has been successfully updated."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster has a solid orange light, it is not connected to Wi-Fi. Check your Internet connection or change to another Wi-Fi network.

If that does not resolve the issue, you can also factory reset your device. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment.

1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange.

2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

Fire TV Blasterのセットアップ中に問題が発生したようです。 次のことを試してください。

1. Fire TV Blasterを充電器から5秒間取り外した後、背後にしっかりと差し込んでください。

2. スマートフォンを再起動してから、再度セットアップします。

問題が解決されない場合は、Amazonテクニカルサポートに連絡してください。"

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

of Fire TV Blasterの前面のランプが点灯していない場合は、電源がオフになっているか、すでに インターネットに接続されています。Fire TV Blasterの下部にあるボタンを1度押してみて、ランプが反応しない場合、 Fire TV Blasterの電源がオフになっています。

1. Fire TV Blasterの電源アダプタを電源コンセントにしっかり差し込み、 電源ケーブルをFire TV Blasterの背面にしっかりと接続してください。

2. 電源がオフになっていた場合は、電源がオンになり、青いランプが3回点滅して起動します。

3. ランプが青と水色で交互に点滅する場合は、Fire TV Blasterの接続をする準備ができたことを示します。

4. 「再試行」をタップします。"

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Fire TV Blasterのランプがオレンジ色に点滅している場合、アップデートが実行されています。

1. オレンジ色のランプの点滅が終わるまでお待ちください。

2. Fire TV Blasterが再起動し、ランプが青く3回点滅したら、デバイスのアップデートが完了したことがわかります。"

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

紫色のライトが点滅している場合、Fire TV Blasterをセットアップ中にタイムアウトしたので、再起動してください。

1. 充電器をコンセントから抜いて、再びコンセントに差し込みます。

2. Fire TV Blasterが再起動し、ライトが青く3回点滅します。

3. ライトが青と水色で交互に点滅したら、Fire TV Blasterは接続する準備ができています。

4. 「再試行」をタップします。"

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

Fire TV BlasterのLEDが赤く点滅している場合、アップデートしてください。

1. 電源コードをコンセントから抜いてから、再度コンセントに差し込みます。

2. Fire TV Blasterが再起動し、LEDが3回青く点滅します。

3. Fire TV BlasterのLEDがオレンジ色に点滅する場合、アップデートされています。

4. Fire TV Blasterが再起動すると、LEDが3回青く点滅し、デバイスのアップデートが完了したことを 示します。"

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Fire TV Blasterにオレンジ色のライトが点灯している場合、Wi-Fiに接続されていません。インターネット接続を確認するか、別のWi-Fiネットワークに変更してください。

この操作を行っても問題が解決されない場合、デバイスを工場出荷時の設定にリセットすることができます。そうするには、エンターテイメント機器を含め、Fire TV Blasterを再度セットアップしてください。

1. Fire TV Blasterの下部にある「リセット」ボタンを20秒押します。LEDが白からオレンジ色に変わって点灯します。

2. ライトがオレンジ色に点滅したら、デバイスのリセットが完了しました。

3. ライトが青と水色で交互に点滅したら、Fire TV Blasterは接続する準備ができています。

4. 「再試行」をタップします。"

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

Eventuell haben Sie bei der Einrichtung von Fire TV Blaster Probleme. Bitte versuchen Sie in diesem Fall Folgendes:

1. Trennen Sie Fire TV Blaster für 5 Sekunden vom Netzteil und stellen Sie dann sicher, dass es fest an der Rückseite eingesteckt ist.

2. Starten Sie Ihr Telefon neu und führen Sie die Einrichtung erneut durch.

Falls das Problem weiterhin besteht, wenden Sie sich an den technischen Support von Amazon."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "Befolgen Sie diese Anleitung, um Fire TV Blaster auf die Werkseinstellungen zurückzusetzen. Bitte beachten Sie, dass Sie dann Fire TV Blaster neu einrichten und Ihre Unterhaltungsgeräte neu konfigurieren müssen."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Drücken Sie 20 Sekunden lang die Rücksetztaste auf der Unterseite von Fire TV Blaster. Die LED wechselt dann von Weiß zu konstant Orange."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. Wenn die LED abwechselnd blau und cyan aufleuchtet, können Sie Fire TV Blaster erneut einrichten."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. Wenn das Licht orange blinkt, wurde das Gerät zurückgesetzt."

"poobe_ir_command_power_on_main" : "Tippen Sie auf die Schaltfläche oben, um %1$s wieder einzuschalten. Dies könnte einige Sekunden dauern."

"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Tippen Sie auf die oben abgebildete Taste. Die Lautstärke des Geräts %1$s sollte zunehmen."

"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Vergewissern Sie sich, dass Fire TV Blaster mit einer Steckdose verbunden ist. Warten Sie, bis das Licht an der Vorderseite von Fire TV Blaster blau und cyan blinkt. Dies kann bis zu zwei Minuten dauern."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

Wenn Sie kein Licht an der Vorderseite von Fire TV Blaster, sehen können, kann es sein, dass das Gerät entweder ausgeschaltet oder bereits mit dem Internet verbunden ist. Drücken Sie kurz die Taste an der Unterseite von Fire TV Blaster. Wenn das Licht nicht reagiert, bedeutet das, dass Fire TV Blaster ausgeschaltet ist.

1. Vergewissern Sie sich, dass das Netzteil von Fire TV Blaster korrekt mit einer funktionierenden Steckdose verbunden ist und dass das Netzkabel an der Rückseite von Fire TV Blaster mit dem Gerät verbunden ist.

2. Wenn das Gerät ausgeschaltet war, wird es eingeschaltet, und das Licht wird dreimal schnell hintereinander blau blinken. Dies bedeutet, dass das Gerät erfolgreich hochgefahren wurde.

3. Wenn Sie ein Licht sehen, das zwischen Blau und Cyan wechselt, ist Fire TV Blaster bereit für die Verbindung.

4. Tippen Sie auf „Erneut versuchen“."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Wenn Fire TV Blaster orange blinkt, wird das Gerät aktualisiert.

1. Warten Sie, bis das orangefarbene Licht nicht mehr blinkt.

2. Fire TV Blaster startet dann neu und zeigt durch dreimaliges blaues Blinken an, dass das Gerät erfolgreich aktualisiert wurde.

3. Tippen Sie auf „Erneut versuchen“."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

Wenn das Licht violett blinkt, bedeutet dies, dass Fire TV Blaster während der Einrichtung die Zeitbegrenzung überschritten hat und neu gestartet werden muss.

1. Stecken Sie das Netzteil aus und erneut ein.

2. Fire TV Blaster wird neu gestartet und das Licht blinkt dreimal blau.

3. Wenn das Licht abwechselnd blau und cyan leuchtet, ist Fire TV Blaster bereit für die Verbindung.

4. Tippen Sie auf „Erneut versuchen“."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

Wenn Fire TV Blaster rot blinkt, muss das Gerät aktualisiert werden.

1. Trennen Sie das Netzkabel und verbinden Sie es erneut.

2. Fire TV Blaster startet dann neu und das Licht blinkt dreimal blau.

3. Wenn Fire TV Blaster orange blinkt, wird das Gerät aktualisiert.

4. Fire TV Blaster startet dann neu und zeigt durch dreimaliges blaues Blinken an, dass das Gerät erfolgreich aktualisiert wurde."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Wenn die LED konstant orange leuchtet, ist Fire TV Blaster nicht mit dem WLAN verbunden. Überprüfen Sie Ihre Internetverbindung oder wechseln Sie zu einem anderen WLAN-Netzwerk.

Bleibt dies erfolglos, können Sie das Gerät auf die Werkseinstellungen zurücksetzen. Bitte beachten Sie, dass Sie danach Fire TV Blaster erneut einrichten und Ihre Home-Entertainment-Geräte neu konfigurieren müssen.

1. Drücken Sie 20 Sekunden lang die Rücksetztaste an der Unterseite von Fire TV Blaster. Die LED wechselt von Weiß zu konstant Orange.

2. Wenn die LED orange blinkt, ist Ihr Gerät zurückgesetzt.

3. Wenn das Licht abwechselnd blau und cyan leuchtet, ist Fire TV Blaster bereit für die Verbindung.

4. Tippen Sie auf „Erneut versuchen“."

1. Wählen Sie in den Einstellungen Ihres Geräts „Bluetooth“.

"poobe_placement_text" : "Fire TV Blaster sollte eine direkte Sichtverbindung haben mit den Geräten, die Sie steuern möchten, und darf nicht hinter Möbeln oder anderen Objekten platziert werden.

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

You may be having trouble setting up your Fire TV Blaster. Please try the following:

1. Remove your Fire TV Blaster from its power adaptor for 5 seconds and then make sure it is securely plugged into the back.

2. Reboot your phone and try the setup again.

If the problem persists, please contact Amazon Technical Support."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "To factory reset your Fire TV Blaster, follow these steps. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. When the LED is flashing blue and cyan, you will be able to set up your Fire TV Blaster again."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset."

"poobe_ir_command_power_on_main" : "Tap the button above to turn your %1$s back on. This could take a few seconds."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_down_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn down."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn up."

"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Make sure Fire TV Blaster is plugged into an electrical socket. Wait for the light on the front of Fire TV Blaster to flash blue and cyan. This may take up to two minutes."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

If you don't see a light in front of Fire TV Blaster, it may either be turned off or already connected to the internet. Quickly press and release the button at the bottom of Fire TV Blaster. If the light does not react, it means Fire TV Blaster is turned off.

1. Check that Fire TV Blaster's power adaptor is properly connected to a working electrical socket and the power cable is securely plugged to the back of Fire TV Blaster.

2. If it was turned off, it will turn on and the light will quickly blink blue three times to indicate it has successfully booted up.

3. When you see the light alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

1. Wait for the orange light to stop blinking.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated.

3. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

If you're seeing a blinking purple light, it means Fire TV Blaster has timed out during setup and must be restarted.

1. Unplug the power adaptor, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking red, it must be updated.

1. Unplug the power cord, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

4. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster has a solid orange light, it is not connected to Wi-Fi. Check your internet connection or change to another Wi-Fi network.

If that does not resolve the issue, you can also factory reset your device. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment.

1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange.

2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_need_bt" : "

Bluetooth should remain on during setup."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

Vous pourriez avoir des difficultés à configurer votre appareil Fire TV Blaster. Veuillez essayer de faire ce qui suit ;

1. Retirez votre appareil Fire TV Blaster de son adaptateur secteur pendant 5 secondes puis assurez-vous qu'il est correctement branché à l'arrière.

2. Redémarrez votre téléphone et réessayez la configuration.

Si le problème persiste, veuillez contacter l'assistance technique d'Amazon."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "Pour restaurer votre appareil Fire TV Blaster aux paramètres d'usine, suivez ces étapes. Notez que cela vous obligera à configurer à nouveau votre Fire TV Blaster, notamment configurer votre équipement de divertissement."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Appuyez sur le bouton Réinitialiser au bas de votre appareil Fire TV Blaster pendant 20 secondes. La LED passera de blanc à orange fixe."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. Lorsque la LED clignote en bleu et cyan, vous pourrez reconfigurer votre appareil Fire TV Blaster."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. Lorsque la lumière clignote en orange, votre appareil est réinitialisé."

"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Assurez-vous que l'appareil Fire TV Blaster est branché à une prise. Patientez jusqu'à ce que le voyant situé sur le devant de l'appareil Fire TV Blaster clignote en bleu et cyan. Cela peut prendre jusqu'à deux minutes."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

Si vous ne voyez pas de voyant sur le devant de votre Fire TV Blaster, il pourrait, soit être éteint, soit déjà connecté à Internet. Appuyez et relâchez rapidement le bouton au bas de l'appareil Fire TV Blaster. Si le voyant ne réagit pas, cela signifie que l'appareil Fire TV Blaster est éteint.

1. Vérifiez que l'adaptateur secteur de l'appareil Fire TV Blaster est correctement branché dans une prise électrique opérationnelle et que le câble d'alimentation est correctement branché à l'arrière de l'appareil Fire TV Blaster.

2. S'il était éteint, il s'allumera et le voyant clignotera rapidement trois fois en bleu pour indiquer qu'il a redémarré correctement

3. Si le voyant alterne entre bleu et cyan, Fire TV Blaster est prêt à être connecté.

4. Touchez réessayer."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Si votre appareil Fire TV Blaster clignote en orange, il est en cours de mise à jour.

1. Patientez jusqu'à ce que le voyant orange cesse de clignoter.

2. Votre appareil Fire TV Blaster redémarrera et le voyant clignotera trois fois en bleu pour indiquer que votre appareil a bien été mis à jour.

3. Touchez Réessayer."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

Si le voyant clignote en violet, cela signifie que l'appareil Fire TV Blaster s'est interrompu pendant la configuration et doit redémarrer.

1. Débranchez, puis rebranchez l'adaptateur secteur.

2. Votre appareil Fire TV Blaster redémarrera et le voyant clignotera trois fois en bleu.

3. Lorsque le voyant alterne entre bleu et cyan, l'appareil Fire TV Blaster est prêt à être connecté.

4. Touchez Réessayer."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

Si votre appareil Fire TV Blaster clignote en rouge, il doit être mis à jour.

1. Débranchez le cordon d'alimentation, puis rebranchez-le.

2. Votre appareil Fire TV Blaster redémarrera et le voyant clignotera en bleu trois fois.

3. Si votre appareil Fire TV Blaster clignote en orange, sa mise à jour est en cours.

4. Votre appareil Fire TV Blaster redémarrera et le voyant clignotera trois fois en bleu pour indiquer que votre appareil a été correctement mis à jour."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Si un voyant orange s'allume en orange sur votre appareil Fire TV Blaster, il n'est pas connecté au Wi-Fi. Vérifiez votre connexion Internet ou connectez-vous à un autre réseau Wi-Fi.

Si le problème persiste, vous pouvez également restaurer votre appareil aux paramètres d'usine. Notez que vous devrez reconfigurer votre appareil Fire TV Blaster, notamment votre équipement de divertissement.

1. Appuyez sur le bouton Réinitialiser au bas de votre appareil Fire TV Blaster pendant 20 secondes. La LED s'allumera en orange.

2. Lorsque le voyant clignote en orange, votre appareil est réinitialisé.

3. Lorsque le voyant clignote en bleu et cyan, l'appareil Fire TV Blaster est prêt pour la connexion.

4. Touchez Réessayer."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

Puede que tengas problemas para configurar el Fire TV Blaster. Prueba lo siguiente:

1. Desconecta el Fire TV Blaster del adaptador de corriente durante 5 segundos y, a continuación, vuelve a conectarlo firmemente en la parte posterior.

2. Reinicia tu teléfono y vuelve a intentar configurar el dispositivo.

Si el problema persiste, ponte en contacto con el soporte técnico de Amazon."

"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. Cuando la luz empiece a parpadear en color naranja, significará que el dispositivo se ha restablecido."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

Si no ves ninguna luz en la parte frontal del Fire TV Blaster, puede que esté apagado o que ya esté conectado a Internet. Pulsa el botón de la parte inferior del Fire TV Blaster. Si la luz no cambia, significa que el Fire TV Blaster está apagado.

1. Comprueba que el adaptador de corriente del Fire TV Blasterestá correctamente enchufado a una toma de corriente que funciona y que el cable de alimentación está bien conectado a la parte posterior del Fire TV Blaster.

2. Si estaba apagado, el dispositivo se encenderá y la luz parpadeará rápidamente de color azul tres veces para indicar que se ha iniciado correctamente.

3. Cuando veas que la luz parpadea de color azul y cian, el Fire TV Blaster estará listo para conectarse.

4. Pulsa Volver a intentarlo."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Si el Fire TV Blaster parpadea de color naranja, está actualizándose.

1. Espera a que la luz naranja deje de parpadear.

2. El Fire TV Blaster se reiniciará y la luz parpadeará tres veces de color azul para indicar que el dispositivo se ha actualizado correctamente.

3. Pulsa Volver a intentarlo."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

Si ves una luz intermitente de color morado, significa que se ha agotado el tiempo de espera para la configuración del Fire TV Blaster y que es necesario reiniciarlo.

1. Desconecta el adaptador de corriente y conéctalo de nuevo.

2. El Fire TV Blaster se reiniciará y la luz parpadeará en color azul tres veces.

3. Cuando la luz parpadee en color azul y cian, el Fire TV Blaster estará listo para conectarse.

4. Pulsa Volver a intentar."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

Si el Fire TV Blaster está parpadeando en color rojo, es necesario actualizarlo.

1. Desconecta el cable de alimentación y vuelve a conectarlo.

2. El Fire TV Blaster se reiniciará y la luz parpadeará tres veces en azul.

3. Si el Fire TV Blaster está parpadeando en naranja, está actualizándose.

4. El Fire TV Blaster se reiniciará y la luz parpadeará tres veces en azul para indicar que el dispositivo se ha actualizado correctamente."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Si el Fire TV Blaster tiene una luz naranja que no parpadea, no está conectado a la red wifi. Comprueba la conexión a Internet o cambia a otra red wifi.

Si eso no resuelve el problema, también puedes restablecer la configuración predeterminada del dispositivo. Ten en cuenta que deberás volver a configurar el Fire TV Blaster y tu equipo de entretenimiento.

1. Mantén pulsado durante 20 segundos el botón de restablecer situado en la parte inferior del Fire TV Blaster. El LED cambiará de blanco a naranja.

2. Cuando la luz empiece a parpadear en color naranja, significará que el dispositivo se ha restablecido.

3. Cuando la luz parpadee en azul y cian, el Fire TV Blaster estará listo para conectarse.

4. Pulsa Volver a intentar."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

Potresti avere dei problemi durante la configurazione di Fire TV Blaster. Prova la seguente procedura:

1. Scollega Fire TV Blaster dal suo alimentatore di corrente per 5 secondi, quindi assicurati che sia collegato saldamente sul retro.

2. Riavvia il telefono e prova a eseguire di nuovo la configurazione.

Se il problema persiste contatta l'assistenza tecnica di Amazon."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "Per ripristinare Fire TV Blaster alle impostazioni di fabbrica, segui i seguenti passaggi. Attenzione: dovrai riconfigurare Fire TV Blaster, compresi i dispositivi per l'intrattenimento."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Premi il pulsante Ripristina sul fondo di Fire TV Blaster per 20 secondi. Il LED passerà da bianco ad arancione a luce fissa."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. Quando il LED lampeggia in blu e celeste, puoi riconfigurare Fire TV Blaster."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. Quando la spia lampeggerà in arancione, il dispositivo sarà stato ripristinato."

"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Tocca il pulsante qui sopra. Il volume del dispositivo %1$s dovrebbe alzarsi."

"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Assicurati che Fire TV Blaster sia collegato a una presa di corrente. Attendi che la spia sulla parte anteriore di Fire TV Blaster lampeggi in blu e celeste. Questa operazione potrebbe richiedere fino a due minuti."
"poobe_led_is_solid_orange" : "La spia ha una luce arancione fissa"

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

Se non vedi una spia sulla parte anteriore di Fire TV Blaster, potrebbe essere spento o già connesso a internet. Premi e rilascia velocemente il pulsante sul fondo di Fire TV Blaster. Se la spia non ha alcuna reazione, significa che Fire TV Blaster è spento.

1. Controlla che l'alimentatore di corrente di Fire TV Blaster sia collegato correttamente a una presa funzionante e che il cavo di alimentazione sia collegato correttamente al retro di Fire TV Blaster.

2. Se era spento, si accenderà e la spia lampeggerà brevemente in blu tre volte per indicare che si è avviato correttamente.

3. Quando vedi la spia che si alterna tra blu e celeste, Fire TV Blaster è pronto a connettersi.

4. Tocca Riprova."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Se Fire TV Blaster lampeggia in arancione, è in aggiornamento.

1. Attendi che la spia arancione smetta di lampeggiare.

2. Fire TV Blaster si riavvierà e la spia lampeggerà in blu tre volte per indicare che il dispositivo è stato aggiornato correttamente."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

Se vedi una spia che lampeggia in viola, significa che Fire TV Blaster ha impiegato troppo tempo per la configurazione e deve essere riavviato.

1. Scollega l'alimentatore di corrente e ricollegalo.

2. Fire TV Blaster si riavvierà e la spia lampeggerà tre volte in blu.

3. Quando la spia si alterna tra blu e celeste, Fire TV Blaster è pronto a connettersi.

4. Tocca Riprova."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

Se Fire TV Blaster lampeggia in rosso, deve essere aggiornato.

1. Scollega il cavo di alimentazione, poi ricollegalo.

2. Fire TV Blaster si riavvierà e la spia lampeggerà in blu tre volte.

3. Se Fire TV Blaster lampeggia in arancione, è in aggiornamento.

4. Fire TV Blaster si riavvierà e la spia lampeggerà in blu tre volte per indicare che il dispositivo è stato aggiornato correttamente."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Se Fire TV Blaster ha una spia arancione fissa, non è connesso al Wi-Fi. Controlla la connessione a Internet o passa a un'altra rete Wi-Fi.

Se in questo modo il problema non si risolve, puoi anche ripristinare il dispositivo alle impostazioni di fabbrica. Attenzione: dovrai riconfigurare Fire TV Blaster, compresi i dispositivi per l'intrattenimento.

1. Premi il pulsante Ripristina sul fondo di Fire TV Blaster per 20 secondi. Il LED passerà da bianco ad arancione a luce fissa.

2. Quando la spia lampeggia in arancione, il dispositivo è stato ripristinato.

3. Quando la spia si alterna tra blu e celeste, Fire TV Blaster è pronto a connettersi.

4. Tocca Riprova."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

You may be having trouble setting up your Fire TV Blaster. Please try the following:

1. Remove your Fire TV Blaster from its power adaptor for 5 seconds and then make sure it is securely plugged into the back.

2. Reboot your phone and try the setup again.

If the problem persists, please contact Amazon Technical Support."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "To factory reset your Fire TV Blaster, follow these steps. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. When the LED is flashing blue and cyan, you will be able to set up your Fire TV Blaster again."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset."

"poobe_ir_command_power_on_main" : "Tap the button above to turn your %1$s back on. This could take a few seconds."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_down_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn down."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn up."

"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Make sure Fire TV Blaster is plugged into an electrical socket. Wait for the light on the front of Fire TV Blaster to flash blue and cyan. This may take up to two minutes."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

If you don't see a light in front of Fire TV Blaster, it may either be turned off or already connected to the internet. Quickly press and release the button at the bottom of Fire TV Blaster. If the light does not react, it means Fire TV Blaster is turned off.

1. Check that Fire TV Blaster's power adaptor is properly connected to a working electrical socket and the power cable is securely plugged to the back of Fire TV Blaster.

2. If it was turned off, it will turn on and the light will quickly blink blue three times to indicate it has successfully booted up.

3. When you see the light alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

1. Wait for the orange light to stop blinking.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated.

3. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

If you're seeing a blinking purple light, it means Fire TV Blaster has timed out during setup and must be restarted.

1. Unplug the power adaptor, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking red, it must be updated.

1. Unplug the power cord, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

4. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster has a solid orange light, it is not connected to Wi-Fi. Check your internet connection or change to another Wi-Fi network.

If that does not resolve the issue, you can also factory reset your device. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment.

1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange.

2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

Vous pourriez avoir des difficultés à configurer votre Fire TV Blaster. Veuillez essayer ce qui suit :

1. Débranchez l'adaptateur secteur du Fire TV Blaster pendant 5 secondes puis rebranchez-le correctement à l'arrière.

2. Redémarrez votre téléphone et réessayez la configuration.

Si le problème persiste, veuillez communiquer avec le soutien technique d'Amazon."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "Pour restaurer votre appareil Fire TV Blaster aux paramètres d'usine, suivez les étapes suivantes. Notez que cela vous obligera à configurer à nouveau votre Fire TV Blaster, notamment configurer votre équipement de divertissement."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Appuyez sur le bouton Réinitialiser situé au-dessous de votre Fire TV Blaster pendant 20 secondes. La DEL passera de blanc à orange fixe."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. Lorsque la DEL clignotera en bleu et cyan, vous pourrez à nouveau configurer votre Fire TV Blaster."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. Lorsque le voyant clignotera en orange, votre appareil sera réinitialisé."

"poobe_ir_command_power_off_main" : "Touchez le bouton ci-dessus. Votre %1$s devrait s'éteindre."
"poobe_ir_command_power_on_main" : "Touchez le bouton ci-dessus pour rallumer votre %1$s. Ceci peut prendre quelques secondes."

"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Touchez le bouton ci-dessus. Le volume de votre %1$s devrait augmenter."

"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Assurez-vous que Fire TV Blaster est branché dans une prise électrique. Patientez jusqu'à ce que le voyant situé sur le devant de votre Fire TV Blaster clignote en bleu et cyan. Cela peut prendre jusqu'à deux minutes."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

Si vous ne voyez pas de voyant à l'avant de votre Fire TV Blaster, il pourrait, soit être éteint, soit déjà connecté à l'Internet. Enfoncez et relâchez rapidement le bouton au bas du Fire TV Blaster. Si le voyant ne réagit pas, cela signifie que Fire TV Blaster est éteint.

1. Vérifiez que l'adaptateur secteur du Fire TV Blaster est correctement branché dans une prise électrique opérationnelle et que le câble d'alimentation est correctement branché à l'arrière du Fire TV Blaster.

2. S'il était éteint, il s'allumera et le voyant clignotera rapidement trois fois en bleu pour indiquer qu'il a redémarré correctement

3. Si le voyant alterne entre bleu et cyan, Fire TV Blaster est prêt à se connecter.

4. Touchez réessayer."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Si votre Fire TV Blaster clignote en orange, il est en cours de mise à jour.

1. Attendez que le voyant orange s'arrête de clignoter.

2. Votre Fire TV Blaster redémarrera et le voyant clignotera en bleu trois fois pour indiquer que votre appareil a bien été mis à jour.

3. Touchez Réessayer."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

Si vous voyez un voyant violet clignotant, cela signifie que Fire TV Blaster s'est éteint en cours de configuration et doit être redémarré.

1. Débranchez puis rebranchez l'adaptateur secteur.

2. Votre Fire TV Blaster redémarrera et le voyant clignotera en bleu trois fois.

3. Lorsque le voyant alternera entre bleu et cyan, Fire TV Blaster sera prêt à se connecter.

4. Touchez réessayer."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

Si votre appareil Fire TV Blaster clignote en rouge, il doit être mis à jour.

1. Débranchez le cordon d'alimentation, puis rebranchez-le.

2. Votre appareil Fire TV Blaster redémarrera et le voyant clignotera en bleu trois fois.

3. Si votre appareil Fire TV Blaster clignote en orange, sa mise à jour est en cours.

4. Votre appareil Fire TV Blaster redémarrera et le voyant clignotera trois fois en bleu pour indiquer que votre appareil a été correctement mis à jour."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Si le voyant de votre Fire TV Blaster est orange fixe, il n'est pas connecté au Wi-Fi. Vérifiez votre connexion Internet ou changez de réseau Wi-Fi.

Si cela ne résout pas le problème, vous pouvez aussi restaurer les paramètres d'usine de votre appareil. Notez qu'il vous faudra configurer à nouveau votre Fire TV Blaster, y compris configurer votre équipement de divertissement.

1. Appuyez sur le bouton Réinitialiser au bas de votre Fire TV Blaster pendant 20 secondes. La DEL passera de blanc à orange fixe.

2. Lorsque la lumière clignote en orange, votre appareil est réinitialisé.

3. Lorsque la lumière alternere entre bleu et cyan, Fire TV Blaster est prêt pour la connexion.

4. Touchez Réessayer."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

You may be having trouble setting up your Fire TV Blaster. Please try the following:

1. Remove your Fire TV Blaster from its power adaptor for 5 seconds and then make sure it is securely plugged into the back.

2. Reboot your phone and try the setup again.

If the problem persists, please contact Amazon Technical Support."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "To factory reset your Fire TV Blaster, follow these steps. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. When the LED is flashing blue and cyan, you will be able to set up your Fire TV Blaster again."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset."

"poobe_ir_command_power_on_main" : "Tap the button above to turn your %1$s back on. This could take a few seconds."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_down_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn down."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn up."

"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Make sure Fire TV Blaster is plugged into an electrical socket. Wait for the light on the front of Fire TV Blaster to flash blue and cyan. This may take up to two minutes."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

If you don't see a light in front of Fire TV Blaster, it may either be turned off or already connected to the internet. Quickly press and release the button at the bottom of Fire TV Blaster. If the light does not react, it means Fire TV Blaster is turned off.

1. Check that Fire TV Blaster's power adaptor is properly connected to a working electrical socket and the power cable is securely plugged to the back of Fire TV Blaster.

2. If it was turned off, it will turn on and the light will quickly blink blue three times to indicate it has successfully booted up.

3. When you see the light alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

1. Wait for the orange light to stop blinking.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated.

3. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

If you're seeing a blinking purple light, it means Fire TV Blaster has timed out during setup and must be restarted.

1. Unplug the power adaptor, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking red, it must be updated.

1. Unplug the power cord, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

4. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster has a solid orange light, it is not connected to Wi-Fi. Check your internet connection or change to another Wi-Fi network.

If that does not resolve the issue, you can also factory reset your device. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment.

1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange.

2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

Você pode estar com problemas para configurar o seu Fire TV Blaster. Tente fazer o seguinte;

1. Remova o seu Fire TV Blaster de seu adaptador de tomada por 5 segundos e depois verifique se ele foi reconectado corretamente na parte traseira.

2. Reinicie o seu telefone e tente configurar novamente.

Se o problema não for solucionado, entre em contato com o suporte técnico da Amazon."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "Para redefinir os dados do seu Fire TV Blaster para os padrões de fábrica, siga os seguintes passos. Observe que isto exigirá que você reconfigure o Fire TV Blaster e o seu equipamento de entretenimento."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Mantenha o botão Reiniciar na parte inferior do seu Fire TV Blaster pressionado por 20 segundos. O LED mudará de branco para laranja fixo."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. Quando o LED estiver piscando azul e ciano, você poderá configurar seu Fire TV Blaster novamente."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. Quando a luz piscar laranja, significa que o dispositivo foi redefinido."
"poobe_fire_tv_redirect_option_message" : "Notamos que você tem um Fire TV vinculado à sua conta. Recomendamos que continue o resto da configuração no seu Fire TV."
"poobe_group_header_text" : "Onde está o seu Fire TV Blaster?"
"poobe_ir_command_power_off_main" : "Toque no botão acima. O dispositivo %1$s deve desligar."
"poobe_ir_command_power_on_main" : "Toque no botão acima para ligar o dispositivo %1$s de novo. Isto pode levar alguns segundos."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_down_main" : "Toque no botão acima. O volume do dispositivo %1$s deve diminuir."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Toque no botão acima. O volume do dispositivo %1$s deve aumentar."

"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Certifique-se de que o Fire TV Blaster está conectado a uma tomada. Espere até a luz na frente do Fire TV Blaster piscar em azul e ciano. Isto pode levar até dois minutos."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

Se não houver uma luz acesa na frente do seu Fire TV Blaster, é possível que ele esteja desligado ou que já esteja conectado à Internet. Pressione e solte rapidamente o botão embaixo do Fire TV Blaster. Se a luz não reagir, significa que o Fire TV Blaster está desligado.

1. Certifique-se de que o adaptador de alimentação do Fire TV Blaster está conectado a uma tomada que esteja funcionando adequadamente e que o cabo de alimentação está conectado à parte de trás do Fire TV Blaster.

2. Se o dispositivo estiver desligado, ele ligará e sua luz piscará em azul três vezes para indicar que foi iniciado com êxito.

3. Quando você vir a luz alternando entre azul e ciano, o Fire TV Blaster está pronto para ser conectado.

4. Toque em Tentar novamente."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Se a luz do seu Fire TV Blaster estiver piscando na cor laranja, significa que ele está atualizando.

1. Aguarde a luz laranja parar de piscar.

2. O seu Fire TV Blaster reiniciará e a luz piscará em azul três vezes, indicando que o dispositivo foi atualizado com êxito.

3. Toque em Tentar novamente."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

Se você estiver vendo uma luz roxa piscando, isso significa que o tempo-limite do Fire TV Blaster expirou e ele precisa ser reiniciado.

1. Desconecte o cabo de energia e depois conecte-o novamente.

2. O seu Fire TV Blaster reiniciará e a luz piscará na cor azul três vezes.

3. Quando a luz alternar entre azul e ciano, o Fire TV Blaster está pronto para se conectar.

4. Toque em Tentar novamente."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

Se o seu Fire TV Blaster estiver piscando na cor vermelha, ele precisa ser atualizado.

1. Desconecte o cabo de energia e depois conecte-o novamente.

2. O seu Fire TV Blaster reiniciará e a luz piscará na cor azul três vezes.

3. Se o seu Fire TV Blaster estiver piscando na cor laranja, isso significa que ele está sendo atualizado.

4. Seu Fire TV Blaster reiniciará e a luz piscará na cor azul três vezes para indicar que o dispositivo foi atualizado."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

Se o seu Fire TV Blaster mostrar uma luz laranja fixa, ele não está conectado a uma rede Wi-Fi. Verifique a conexão com a Internet ou tente outra rede Wi-Fi.

Se isso não solucionar o problema, você também pode redefinir os dados do dispositivo para o padrão de fábrica. Observe que isso exigirá que você configure o Fire TV Blaster novamente, inclusive reconfigurando seu equipamento de entretenimento.

1. Mantenha o botão Redefinir na parte inferior do Fire TV Blaster pressionado por 20 segundos. O LED mudará da cor branca para laranja fixo.

2. Quando a luz piscar na cor laranja, seu dispositivo foi redefinido.

3. Quando a luz alternar entre azul e ciano, o Fire TV Blaster está pronto para conectar.

4. Toque em Tentar novamente."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

You may be having trouble setting up your Fire TV Blaster. Please try the following;

1. Remove your Fire TV Blaster from it's power adapter for 5 seconds and then make sure is securely plugged to the back.

2. Reboot your phone and try the setup again.

If the problem still persists please contact Amazon Technical Support."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "To factory reset your Fire TV Blaster, follow these steps. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. When the LED is flashing blue and cyan, you will be able to set up your Fire TV Blaster again."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset."
"poobe_fire_tv_redirect_option_message" : "We noticed that you have a Fire TV linked to your account. We recommend that you continue the rest of setup on your Fire TV."
"poobe_ir_command_power_off_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s should turn off."
"poobe_ir_command_power_on_main" : "Tap the button above to turn your %1$s back on. This could take a few seconds."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_down_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn down."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn up."
"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Make sure Fire TV Blaster is plugged into an outlet. Wait for the light on the front of Fire TV Blaster to flash blue and cyan. This may take up to two minutes."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

If you don't see a light in front of Fire TV Blaster, it could be either powered off or already connected to the internet. Quickly press and release the button at the bottom of Fire TV Blaster. If the light does not react, it means Fire TV Blaster is powered off.

1. Check that Fire TV Blaster's power adapter is properly connected to a working outlet and the power cable is securely plugged to the back of Fire TV Blaster.

2. If it was powered off, it will turn on and the light will quickly blink blue three times to indicate it has successfully booted up.

3. When you see the light alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

1. Wait for the orange light to stop blinking.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated.

3. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

If you're seeing a blinking purple light, it means Fire TV Blaster has timed out during setup and must be restarted.

1. Unplug the power adapter, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking red, it must be updated.

1. Unplug the power cord, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

4. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will turn off to indicate that your device has been successfully updated."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster has a solid orange light, it is not connected to Wi-Fi. Check your Internet connection or change to another Wi-Fi network.

If that does not resolve the issue, you can also factory reset your device. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment.

1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange.

2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_discovery_troubleshoot" : "

You may be having trouble setting up your Fire TV Blaster. Please try the following:

1. Remove your Fire TV Blaster from its power adaptor for 5 seconds and then make sure it is securely plugged into the back.

2. Reboot your phone and try the setup again.

If the problem persists, please contact Amazon Technical Support."

"poobe_factory_reset_main_text" : "To factory reset your Fire TV Blaster, follow these steps. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_one" : "1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_three" : "3. When the LED is flashing blue and cyan, you will be able to set up your Fire TV Blaster again."
"poobe_factory_reset_step_two" : "2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset."
"poobe_fire_tv_redirect_option_message" : "We noticed that you have a Fire TV linked to your account. We recommend that you continue setup on your Fire TV."

"poobe_ir_command_power_on_main" : "Tap the button above to turn your %1$s back on. This could take a few seconds."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_down_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn down."
"poobe_ir_command_volume_up_main" : "Tap the button above. Your %1$s volume should turn up."

"poobe_led_check_main_text" : "Make sure Fire TV Blaster is plugged into an electrical socket. Wait for the light on the front of Fire TV Blaster to flash blue and cyan. This may take up to two minutes."

"poobe_led_missing_troubleshoot" : "

If you don't see a light in front of Fire TV Blaster, it may either be turned off or already connected to the internet. Quickly press and release the button at the bottom of Fire TV Blaster. If the light does not react, it means Fire TV Blaster is turned off.

1. Check that Fire TV Blaster's power adaptor is properly connected to a working electrical socket and the power cable is securely plugged to the back of Fire TV Blaster.

2. If it was turned off, it will turn on and the light will quickly blink blue three times to indicate it has successfully booted up.

3. When you see the light alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

1. Wait for the orange light to stop blinking.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated.

3. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_purple_troubleshoot" : "

If you're seeing a blinking purple light, it means Fire TV Blaster has timed out during setup and must be restarted.

1. Unplug the power adaptor, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

"poobe_led_red_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking red, it must be updated.

1. Unplug the power cord, then plug it back in.

2. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times.

3. If your Fire TV Blaster is blinking orange, it is being updated.

4. Your Fire TV Blaster will restart and the light will blink blue three times to indicate that your device has been successfully updated."

"poobe_led_solid_orange_troubleshoot" : "

If your Fire TV Blaster has a solid orange light, it is not connected to Wi-Fi. Check your internet connection or change to another Wi-Fi network.

If that does not resolve the issue, you can also factory reset your device. Note that this will require you to set up your Fire TV Blaster again, including configuring your entertainment equipment.

1. Press the Reset button on the bottom of your Fire TV Blaster for 20 seconds. The LED will change from white to solid orange.

2. When the light blinks orange, your device has been reset.

3. When the light is alternating between blue and cyan, Fire TV Blaster is ready to connect.

4. Tap Retry."

playstore_details.title: Amazon Fire TV
playstore_details.description:
The free Amazon Fire TV mobile app for iOS/Android/Fire OS enhances your  Fire TV experience with simple navigation, a keyboard for easy text entry (no more hunting and pecking), and quick access to your favorite apps and games.

It features:

    Voice search (not available in all countries)
    Simple navigation
    Playback controls
    Keyboard for simple text entry
    Quick access to your apps and games

Compatibility:

• Multicast-enabled router required
• Designed for simple navigation and playback control of Fire TV streaming media players
• For gameplay, use the remote included with your Fire TV or the optional Amazon Fire TV Game Controller
playstore_details.summary: Simple navigation, a keyboard, plus voice search for Fire TV.
